34
00:05:13,207 --> 00:05:16,587
Inside this suitcase are things that can be used regularly.

35
00:05:16,587 --> 00:05:21,747
Like band-aids, cold medicine, and a set of sheets and quilt covers.

36
00:05:21,747 --> 00:05:24,900
That suitcase is filled with clothes.

37
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:29,165
- You are like my mom now. 
 - It's good to be prepared, right?

38
00:05:29,165 --> 00:05:32,227
Anyway, the items in that suitcase will all come in handy.

39
00:05:32,227 --> 00:05:36,292
If your classmates need anything, give it directly to them and be nice.

40
00:05:36,292 --> 00:05:40,530
By the way, the school usually provides bed sheets and quilt covers. But the quality of those is not good.

41
00:05:40,530 --> 00:05:43,947
Just switch to your own. If you need anything, call me.

42
00:05:43,947 --> 00:05:46,947
I don't lack anything. I don't need these things.

43
00:05:46,947 --> 00:05:49,007
Take them.

44
00:05:49,007 --> 00:05:53,047
Just listen to Xiao Que. She has the experience of college life.

45
00:05:53,047 --> 00:05:56,947
- Once you're there, you'll know if you need them or not. 
 - That's right.

46
00:05:57,547 --> 00:06:01,167
Grandpa, Xiao Ye will go to college tomorrow. Why not stay a few more days?

47
00:06:01,167 --> 00:06:03,187
What's the rush to leave?

48
00:06:03,187 --> 00:06:06,707
You make me sound utterly idle. I'm busy.

49
00:06:06,707 --> 00:06:10,807
The gateball competition offers points and a bonus this year.

50
00:06:10,807 --> 00:06:14,967
- A bonus? How much is it? 
 - No, it's a 380-yuan assorted grain gift pack.

51
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:17,627
- It's so expensive? 
 - It's a huge pack.

52
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:21,527
I just came to see you guys. I'm just glad you guys are doing well.

53
00:06:21,527 --> 00:06:24,447
- I'll come when I have time. 
 - Okay.

54
00:06:24,447 --> 00:06:27,627
Then, when you come, let me know, so I can pick you up.

55
00:06:27,627 --> 00:06:30,487
No need. I can come by myself.

56
00:06:31,627 --> 00:06:35,167
It's so late. Why isn't Xiao Tuo back yet?

57
00:06:36,347 --> 00:06:40,507
He's been working overtime frequently. You should go to sleep.

58
00:06:40,507 --> 00:06:44,327
You should go to sleep too. You need to get up early. Go wash up now.

59
00:06:44,327 --> 00:06:47,507
- It's still early. 
 - Hurry up.

60
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:50,147
- Hurry up. Wash first. 
 - Hurry up.

61
00:06:50,147 --> 00:06:53,627
- Let me finish this part. 
 - I'll be with you.

62
00:07:00,767 --> 00:07:04,527
Go back. You still have work to do. Just stay.

63
00:07:04,527 --> 00:07:06,307
We'll see you off.

64
00:07:06,307 --> 00:07:10,207
I'm not senile. I don't need it.

65
00:07:10,207 --> 00:07:13,367
Hurry back. Take care of yourself.

66
00:07:13,367 --> 00:07:15,567
Take good care of Xiao Ye, okay?

67
00:07:15,567 --> 00:07:17,747
Don't worry, Grandpa.

68
00:07:18,707 --> 00:07:22,227
Goodbye, Grandpa. Let us know if you arrive.

69
00:07:22,227 --> 00:07:24,040
Take care.

70
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,080
Let's go.

71
00:07:34,127 --> 00:07:36,687
Did Xu Tianhai get married?

72
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:47,785
Did Xu Tianhai get married and then divorce?

73
00:07:47,785 --> 00:07:50,465
Or did he never marry at all?

74
00:07:51,171 --> 00:07:55,171
He said his mom was pressuring him to get married in Moments last week.

75
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:59,827
If you haven't seen that post, you can check your phone right now.

76
00:07:59,827 --> 00:08:03,727
Lin Tuo, whose wedding ceremony did you go to attend?

77
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:08,027
Say something. What have you done on those days?

78
00:08:08,027 --> 00:08:09,967
Why did you have to lie to me like this?

79
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:12,067
You came back and broke up with me.

80
00:08:12,067 --> 00:08:14,587
Where on earth did you go?

81
00:08:19,413 --> 00:08:23,227
- We have already broken up. 
 - Is this the reason for the breakup?

82
00:08:25,527 --> 00:08:28,097
He Xindi is right.

83
00:08:28,097 --> 00:08:30,587
No wonder you can't explain it to me.

84
00:08:30,587 --> 00:08:32,807
No wonder you are so resolute.

85
00:08:32,807 --> 00:08:35,687
I wondered if there was some misunderstanding between us,

86
00:08:35,687 --> 00:08:38,287
if I didn't do well enough and I had neglected you,

87
00:08:38,287 --> 00:08:41,387
and if I should try to win you back.

88
00:08:41,387 --> 00:08:44,907
I now feel like I overthought.

89
00:08:44,907 --> 00:08:48,847
Lin Tuo, you can break up with me.

90
00:08:48,847 --> 00:08:52,747
But you lied to me, and let me down.

91
00:09:39,567 --> 00:09:43,047
- Stop. 
 - What's up?

92
00:09:43,047 --> 00:09:45,847
Come here and sit down.

93
00:09:45,847 --> 00:09:48,247
What's up?

94
00:09:48,247 --> 00:09:51,060
I have to ask you something. Sit down.

95
00:09:55,047 --> 00:09:56,567
What's up with Lin Tuo?

96
00:09:56,567 --> 00:09:58,727
What do you mean?

97
00:09:58,727 --> 00:10:02,727
Chen Guangpu, tell me the truth. What exactly happened to Lin Tuo?

98
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:06,187
What are you talking about?

99
00:10:07,087 --> 00:10:09,867
Fine, you're not telling, right?

100
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:13,027
Listen, Chen Guangpu. I've figured this thing out.

101
00:10:15,527 --> 00:10:17,047
What do you mean?

102
00:10:17,047 --> 00:10:19,407
You may fool Xiao Que, but you can't fool me.

103
00:10:19,407 --> 00:10:21,947
I saw through the coldness and warmth of life in my teens.

104
00:10:21,947 --> 00:10:25,300
My mom got married twice. My dad got married three times. I've been in so many relationships.

105
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:27,287
I understand men too well.

106
00:10:27,287 --> 00:10:29,667
There's no such thing as breaking up for no reason.

107
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:32,567
I'm telling you, I have the evidence.

108
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:36,607
Evidence? What is it?

109
00:10:36,607 --> 00:10:40,287
I told Xiao Que to think properly

110
00:10:40,287 --> 00:10:44,680
if Lin Tuo has had any unusual behavior and if he's disappeared recently.

111
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:49,207
She told me Lin Tuo had been in his classmate's wedding ceremony for a few days.

112
00:10:49,207 --> 00:10:52,047
I told her there's something fishy about it.

113
00:10:52,047 --> 00:10:54,827
Guess what? That classmate is abroad.

114
00:10:54,827 --> 00:10:58,807
He doesn't even have a girlfriend. So Lin Tuo got caught right away.

115
00:10:58,807 --> 00:11:01,467
No secrets are safe in this world.

116
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:04,787
So what was Lin Tuo doing during those days?

117
00:11:04,787 --> 00:11:08,340
He went home for a blind date, didn't he? And he found the match, right?

118
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:11,627
After that, he came back and broke up with Xiao Que.

119
00:11:11,627 --> 00:11:15,247
He Xindi, you're really wasting your talent doing livestreaming.

120
00:11:15,247 --> 00:11:17,047
You should write movie scripts.

121
00:11:17,047 --> 00:11:19,307
My analysis is right, isn't it?

122
00:11:20,387 --> 00:11:23,347
I'm truly impressed.

123
00:11:23,347 --> 00:11:26,667
He Xindi, I underestimated you before.

124
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:28,627
You're not ordinary.

125
00:11:28,627 --> 00:11:31,527
Hurry to the hospital. Get treatment early.

126
00:11:31,527 --> 00:11:34,020
Alzheimer is now affects younger individuals.

127
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:38,147
What? Stop the gibberish. Chen Guangpu. I just got it correctly.

128
00:12:36,047 --> 00:12:38,827
 The situation is starting to get bad. 

129
00:12:38,827 --> 00:12:41,567
 You need to be mentally prepared. 

130
00:12:49,190 --> 00:12:53,480
   

131
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,284
   

132
00:12:55,284 --> 00:13:02,410
   

133
00:13:02,410 --> 00:13:03,767
Mom.

134
00:13:03,767 --> 00:13:06,427
 What's wrong? I have to do ward rounds right away. 

135
00:13:06,427 --> 00:13:09,027
 By the way, has Xiao Ye gone to college? 

136
00:13:09,027 --> 00:13:13,127
- Yes, he has. 
 -  That's good. You should visit Xiao Ye more on the weekends. 

137
00:13:13,127 --> 00:13:15,327
 It's his first time leaving home. 

138
00:13:15,327 --> 00:13:18,367
 Now he still has bad feelings towards me and your dad. 

139
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:21,187
 I wanted to take him to college, but he wouldn't let me. 

140
00:13:21,187 --> 00:13:24,327
-  I'll see him next month.  
 - Mom,

141
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:29,840
I'm sick.

142
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:33,500
   

143
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,487
 It's ALS. 

144
00:13:39,010 --> 00:13:43,470
   

145
00:15:23,347 --> 00:15:26,667
Mom, it's okay.

146
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:32,067
Look at me. Except for my right hand, other part is fine, right?

147
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:36,567
Look at my legs. I can stand and walk.

148
00:15:36,567 --> 00:15:40,245
I'm fine. I can also lift my legs high.

149
00:15:42,547 --> 00:15:44,907
Although a bit slower,

150
00:15:44,907 --> 00:15:48,387
my left hand is quite skilled now. I can cook and write with it.

151
00:15:48,387 --> 00:15:52,787
By the way, let me show you what I've written with my left hand.

152
00:15:54,187 --> 00:15:58,307
Here. Take a look. Not bad, right?

153
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:05,220
Anyway, it's legible.

154
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:12,687
Why are you crying again, Mom?

155
00:16:12,687 --> 00:16:14,640
It's okay.

156
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:24,027
You've always been like this.

157
00:16:24,027 --> 00:16:26,487
You never talk about anything.

158
00:16:27,127 --> 00:16:30,720
You won't tell us where you're going or what you're going to do.

159
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:35,400
Faced with such a big issue, you still wouldn't tell us.

160
00:16:36,243 --> 00:16:40,300
Haven't I already told you?

161
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,600
Why didn't you say it earlier?

162
00:16:43,356 --> 00:16:46,676
Why didn't you say it right away?

163
00:16:47,307 --> 00:16:53,047
Are you a child without a family? Don't you have parents?

164
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:03,520
Are you silly?

165
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,920
I do have a family, Mom.

166
00:17:07,066 --> 00:17:10,847
And that's why I couldn't tell you about it.

167
00:17:15,507 --> 00:17:17,207
Mom.

168
00:17:18,907 --> 00:17:21,266
If I didn't tell you,

169
00:17:22,380 --> 00:17:25,100
I wouldn't be able to hug you again.

170
00:17:27,347 --> 00:17:29,126
Xiao Tuo,

171
00:17:31,687 --> 00:17:33,820
don't be afraid.

172
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:35,680
Don't be afraid.

173
00:17:36,607 --> 00:17:41,347
I'm here. I'm right here.

174
00:17:41,347 --> 00:17:45,407
Don't be afraid.

175
00:18:05,947 --> 00:18:07,787
Dad.

176
00:18:07,787 --> 00:18:11,367
Weren't you on a business trip?

177
00:18:14,347 --> 00:18:17,427
W-Where are your medical records?

178
00:18:19,187 --> 00:18:21,027
Medical records?

179
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:25,007
They're in the box under the coffee table.

180
00:18:27,547 --> 00:18:29,967
The password is 1105.

181
00:18:33,151 --> 00:18:35,696
   

182
00:18:37,935 --> 00:18:39,805
   

183
00:18:39,805 --> 00:18:41,670
   

184
00:18:44,967 --> 00:18:49,167
Wash your face and brush your teeth. I bought breakfast.

185
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:51,407
Have something first.

186
00:18:52,847 --> 00:18:55,327
Lin Tuo, I bought you...

187
00:18:57,567 --> 00:19:01,627
Guangpu, they are my parents.

188
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:04,747
Hello, Uncle, Auntie.

189
00:19:04,747 --> 00:19:09,227
This is my classmate in college and my good friend, Chen Guangpu.

190
00:19:09,227 --> 00:19:12,067
In case something happens to me...

191
00:19:13,180 --> 00:19:15,680
He knows the password here.

192
00:19:16,447 --> 00:19:18,927
I'm here to pick him up for work.

193
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:22,980
You shouldn't go to work now.

194
00:19:24,056 --> 00:19:26,947
- Let's go to the hospital. 
 - Dad, I'm still doing okay now.

195
00:19:26,947 --> 00:19:32,387
I can continue to work. There's no use going to the hospital. I'm taking the medicine.

196
00:19:32,387 --> 00:19:35,307
Which hospital and which doctor?

197
00:19:37,227 --> 00:19:39,267
Neurology Department of Baihui Hospital.

198
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:42,787
Dr. Zhou Fumeng. He is the chief physician.

199
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:52,407
Leave it to me.

200
00:19:55,107 --> 00:19:57,627
- Is it too tight? 
 - It's fine.

201
00:19:59,787 --> 00:20:03,267
Why is your dad still so harsh?

202
00:20:03,267 --> 00:20:06,407
You're ill, and he still doesn't treat you kindly.

203
00:20:09,987 --> 00:20:13,967
When my mom gave birth to me and Xiao Ye, my dad was on business trips.

204
00:20:13,967 --> 00:20:18,147
My mom went to the hospital and went back home alone after giving birth.

205
00:20:19,247 --> 00:20:21,507
Although my mom worked at the hospital,

206
00:20:21,507 --> 00:20:25,867
she told me she felt particularly helpless,

207
00:20:25,867 --> 00:20:28,727
and felt like she married the wrong guy.

208
00:20:29,787 --> 00:20:32,047
When Xiao Ye and I were sick back then,

209
00:20:32,047 --> 00:20:36,727
it was always my mom who held both of us, running up and down in the hospital.

210
00:20:36,727 --> 00:20:40,027
In my memory, my dad hardly ever took care of us.

211
00:20:42,627 --> 00:20:46,467
This is the first time I've seen my dad come back in the middle of a business trip.

212
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:50,567
His eyes are bloodshot.

213
00:20:52,827 --> 00:20:55,427
He definitely didn't sleep all night.

214
00:21:01,167 --> 00:21:05,127
Thankfully, both your parents are doctors. They know a lot.

215
00:21:05,127 --> 00:21:11,347
If this happened to me, my parents would probably do nothing but cry.

216
00:21:14,427 --> 00:21:16,407
Even the doctors

217
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,167
can't help with my illness.

218
00:21:20,147 --> 00:21:23,567
Don't talk nonsense. Do you hear me?

219
00:21:24,987 --> 00:21:28,387
Let's go to work.

220
00:21:29,387 --> 00:21:31,487
Grab my hand tightly.

221
00:21:32,867 --> 00:21:34,907
This side.

222
00:21:34,907 --> 00:21:36,527
Tightly.

223
00:21:37,347 --> 00:21:42,167
Not bad. There hasn't been much change. You need to adjust your condition.

224
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:46,807
 Especially, get your eating and sleeping in order, okay? 

225
00:21:46,807 --> 00:21:48,824
 Take the medicine. 

226
00:21:48,824 --> 00:21:51,447
   

227
00:21:51,447 --> 00:21:54,527
 - Okay, that's it. 
 - Thank you, Dr. Zhou. 

228
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:03,365
Director Zhou, I am Lin Tuo's father.

229
00:22:03,365 --> 00:22:05,310
Do you have time right now?

230
00:22:05,310 --> 00:22:07,010
Please come in.

231
00:22:26,047 --> 00:22:30,207
You weren't in your seat, so I thought you are here. What's wrong?

232
00:22:30,207 --> 00:22:33,787
It's nothing. I just came out for fresh air.

233
00:22:33,787 --> 00:22:35,387
Your arm hasn't healed?

234
00:22:35,387 --> 00:22:37,947
Such an injury usually takes months to heal.

235
00:22:39,047 --> 00:22:43,087
By the way, my friend's club has a soccer match this weekend.

236
00:22:43,087 --> 00:22:47,487
They are friends I usually play with. If you're free, come along with Guangpu.

237
00:22:47,487 --> 00:22:50,427
With my current condition, I can't play soccer.

238
00:22:50,427 --> 00:22:53,002
Come as a substitute. I'll introduce you to some friends.

239
00:22:53,002 --> 00:22:56,227
They are all designers and some business partners.

240
00:22:56,227 --> 00:22:59,127
Get to know them. We can play soccer when your arm heals.

241
00:22:59,127 --> 00:23:03,007
- You haven't played for a long time. 
 - That's right.

242
00:23:03,007 --> 00:23:06,307
I've looked over Lin Tuo's medical records.

243
00:23:06,307 --> 00:23:09,327
I've collected some other case studies.

244
00:23:09,327 --> 00:23:11,607
Look, there are even some from abroad.

245
00:23:11,607 --> 00:23:15,567
These are cases of ALS and some related papers.

246
00:23:15,567 --> 00:23:18,507
I'm not sure if they are useful or not.

247
00:23:18,507 --> 00:23:21,007
I can understand how you feel.

248
00:23:21,007 --> 00:23:26,287
But as for Lin Tuo's diagnosis, it's been over half a year.

